evidence: You are asked to look at the five frequencies shown in the figure above and then state the order of the T1 and T2 relaxation times.
In problem 4.8, you are working with hydrogen nuclei in fat and water. You are told that the T2 value of fat is 100 milliseconds and the T2 value of water is 500 milliseconds.

Finally, in problem 4.9, you are asked to write an expression for the longitudinal magnetization, M z, as a function of time after a one-eighty-degree pulse. You should then determine the time at which M z becomes zero.
The goal here is to compare how different tissues relax under different frequencies
